  "relevant_summary": "The evidence for actions to mitigate service corridor impacts on peatland vegetation is extremely limited. Only one study was found that evaluated restoration of water flow across service corridors. In this single before-and-after study in a USA fen, restoring water inflow across a road (along with general rewetting) increased cover of wet peatland sedges while decreasing cover of grasses preferring drier conditions. However, no evidence was found for several key mitigation actions: no studies evaluated retaining/creating habitat corridors across service corridors, backfilling pipeline trenches, or designing transportation corridors to maintain water flow in peatlands. Multiple actions show no available evidence including habitat corridor creation, trench backfilling, and contaminated site cleanup.",
